  "name": "Second Save (Mythic)",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/skills/mech_12.jpg",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Whenever the creature fails a saving throw against an effect with a duration greater than 1 round, it can keep trying to shake off the effect. At the start of its turn, if it&rsquo;s still affected, it can attempt the save one more time as a free action. If this save succeeds, the effect affects the creature as if it had succeeded at its initial saving throw. If the effect already allows another saving throw on a later turn to break the effect (such as for <a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-image: none; background-color: initial; padding: 0px; color: #ff6400; border: none;\" draggable=\"false\" data-pack=\"pf1.spells\" data-id=\"d8hypv6zdyan3rzr\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; text-decoration-line: underline;\">hold monster</span></a>), this ability is in addition to the extra saving throw from the effect.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Format</em>: second save</p>\n<p><em>Location</em>: After saving throws.</p>",
